---
---

<section class="py-16">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="relative bg-bg-low border border-[var(--border-dim)] px-14 py-12 overflow-hidden
                max-sm:px-6 max-sm:py-8">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 text-[48px] font-bold uppercase text-text
                  opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none select-none tracking-[-0.04em]"
           aria-hidden="true">
        MANIFESTO
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-[720px]">
        <div class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-secondary mb-5">
          cat engineer_manifesto.md
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-[clamp(28px,4vw,40px)] font-bold tracking-[-0.04em] uppercase mb-7 leading-[1.05]">
          PLATFORM AS A<br />FORCE MULTIPLIER
        </h2>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-text-muted leading-[1.7] italic
                    border-l-2 border-border pl-6 mb-7">
          <p class="text-[15px]">
            "The platform's job is to disappear. When developers ship without thinking about
            infrastructure, the platform has done its job. Every manual step, every tribal
            knowledge dependency, every ticket to the platform team — is a bug."
          </p>
          <p class="text-[15px]">
            "Complexity is the enemy of reliability. We don't add observability after the fact.
            We don't bolt on security. We don't optimize after the outage. We build it in from
            the start, or we accept the consequences."
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5 font-mono text-[13px] text-text-muted">
          <p>1. Automate or it will bite you at 3am.</p>
          <p>2. GitOps over ClickOps — if it's not in git, it doesn't exist.</p>
          <p>3. Observability over intuition. Alert on symptoms, not causes.</p>
          <p>4. Developer experience is platform correctness.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
